THIRDREALITY
  • Note: Only Support 2.4GHz WiFi.
  • Easy Installation: No wiring required. Snaps on top of an existing toggle or rocker light switch and mechanically controls the underlying switch. If you have any issues, please feel free to contact us.
  • Improved Design &Widely Compatible: No neutral wire required. Works with any voltage (12v, 24v, 110v, 220v). Ideal solution for low-voltage switches like those used with gas fireplaces. Fit 2-gang, 3-gang or 4-gang switches. Upgrade your home lighting with the advanced and versatile Third Reality Smart Switch.
  • Smart Home Assistant Supported: Equipped with a bridge for superior compatibility across a wide array of smart home platforms, including Amazon Alexa, Google Assistant, Apple HomeKit, Samsung SmartThings and Hubitat, for seamless smart home integration.
  • Multiple Light Control Ways, Make Your Life Smarter: Third Reality Smart Switch is an elegant solution for automating your lights without the need to replace or rewire existing switches. Using reliable, low-power ZigBee wireless technology to communicate with Third Reality hub. Enabling you to turn lights on/off with smarter ways, voice control, app control, groups, timers or schedules, etc.
  • Included In-Box: Zigbee Switch*1, Bridge*1, AAA batteriy *2, mounting hardware (fasteners, spacers, screws and protective film)

Product description

Elevate your home lighting with the THIRDREALITY Starter Kit MK5 for Smart Switch Gen3. This versatile solution automates wall switches, featuring a Zigbee Switch, Smart Bridge MZ1, and all necessary hardware for seamless installation. With compatibility across various voltages (12v, 24v, 110v, 220v) and no need for a neutral wire, the MK5 adapts effortlessly to your home.


Matter Supported via Smart Bridge

The THIRDREALITY Smart Bridge MZ1 ensures seamless integration with Apple Home, Google Home and SmartThings. Enjoy smooth LAN control, Multi-Admin access, easy guided installation, and the convenience of voice control. Monitor and manage your lights from anywhere with advanced scheduling and timer options, providing a heightened level of control and accessibility to your smart home setup.


Easy, No Wire Installation

Third Reality Smart Switch Gen3 uses a patentd mechanism that fits over existing toggle or rocker switches and installs in seconds. You don’t need to replace your old wall switch and no electrical work required. Smart Switch Gen3 don't need a backplane anymore. The installation procedure is safe, simple and zero damage to the wall. And renters, when you move you can easily take your Reality Smart Switches with you!


Long Battery Life

Using two AAA standard batteries, the batteries life can last for up to1 years in normal use.


Group Control

With successful pairing wirh THIRDREALITY Smart Bridge, then eable to compatible matter controller you can combine the Third Reality switches into a group to build your smart home lighting system. Easily turn the the lights all on or off.


Timer & Schedule

Set normal timer to turn on/off the light according of your schedules. E.g. When the sun goes down, the lights will be turned on automatically.

---Set and Change Timers Easily via Third Reality APP


Home Automation

Smart switches seamlessly integrate with platforms like Apple Home and Google Home. Choose to add THIRDREALITY sensor products and embark on a comprehensive smart living experience, enabling even more life-like scenarios!

    I had high hopes with these and really worked hard with them but with no real luck. Simply put the hub would pair with one or two or sometimes three (I had bought an extra switch mechanism over what is in the kit) but never managed to stay connected for more than an hour and sometimes as little as a few minutes. This is not a good result for something being installed as a security precaution to turn on porch and deck lights and floodlights. I finally wound up sending the hub to the recycling center in the sky and using the Zigbee capability of my "Alexa" speakers. This worked perfectly and has continued to do so. If I had known I could have saved the money for the hub. Oh, BTW, the switch-activating modules work just fine with the only slight downside being a second of gear sounds when they are operating but that isn't really much of a drawback. Installation of those is simple and seems flexible.
